system_name: RIS - Medics Premier Radiology Information Tracking System
sn_value:
The Radiology Information System (RIS), currently built with Medics Premier version 9.01.002.18 as the only software version validated for use, is designed to track individual patient studies using a unique case number.  The RIS provides a single location for case information and reports and track all steps for image processing and analysis with an audit trail.  It is implemented as an on-premise client/server solution with a Microsoft SQL Server Express database installed on the application server.

See KB0023578 for support and routing guidance.

The RIS provides a single location for case information and reports and track all steps for image processing and analysis with an audit trail.  It is implemented as an on-premise client/server solution with a Microsoft SQL Server Express database installed on the application server.    See KB0023578 for support and routing guidance.

sn_value:
Vertex indirect O Series provides tax amounts for the US and Canada.  Failure of this application will prevent the processing of sales orders and any process requiring tax information in E1.  Incorrect or wrongly stated tax amounts can be penalized by the individual US states and/or Canadian tax authority.  

There are only a handful (< 10) of associates that have access to the actual application itself.  It provides a web service that is configured within the E1 logic servers and makes thousands of calls a day for tax information.  The web services currently reside on the E1 JAS server and the database is in the E1 database.

We currently have a non-production installation serving the Development, Prototype/CRP, Validation and Training E1 environments.  We also have a load balanced production instance servicing production only.  The Vertex application currently resides on AIX 7.1 servers.

sn_value:
Log to track drawing versions. 
Clark Manlove and Don Dixon are in business. Don D. working with Vendor. Written in Clipper!
Don Dixon: We developed 3DCS (Drafting Department Document Control System) in the late 1980's using a commercial program called dBase on the MS-DOS operating system.  It originally ran in the dBase software but was later compiled to run independently on DOS.  The program runs now in a DOS emulator since current Windows environment will not permit it. Within the GMCA Microwave Assembly business, it is used to create and manage engineering drawings, mostly Gore designed microwave connector components.  It contains document numbers, revision histories, and several cross-references particular to the GMCA business.
June 22nd 2021 Sue G., Maria K., Stefan Y.: We try to connect Don and DJ for an feasibility assessment, that in fall we can get it out from Excel and into Adept. If we retire Don would not want this have been for 6 months being retired, therefore we keep it until Adept will replace it.
=> going to ADEPT!

"Enhesa does the following:
• Provides a global view of EH&S Compliance
• Determines the applicability of regulations
• Provides understanding of global requirements and ability to verify compliance
• Proactively tracks and manages regulatory changes and emerging issues to provide ongoing compliance assurance.  
Compliance Intelligence Services includes:  
• Regulatory Foundations – A list of all EHS laws within scope.
• Applicability Screening Questions - Filter out irrelevant regulations or requirements.
• Requirements – Compliance questions, Guide Notes, Regulatory Citations and an indication of Required Documentation.
• Quarterly Updates & Change Notification - Enhesa will update and flag changes in regulations and requirements.
• Client Services Training & Support"

[Note:  FirstUp is the name of the vendor mobile application.  Gore will be changing the mobile app name to something that is more Gore-specific by October 2020.]
FirstUp is mobile application that is part of the SocialChorus Suite.
SocialChorus is a suite of tools that allows the Enterprise Communication team to plan, create, publish, and measure the impact of Enterprise communications from one place.  
The mobile app allows users to receive real-time, Enterprise-wide news and alerts. 
The mobile app connects unwired employees in an elegant way and pairs nicely with desktop, email, and intranet experiences to help reach employees wherever they are.
The Enterprise Communications team uses SocialChorus Studio to send news and alerts to FirstUp.
Additional details can be found at the following link:  https://www.socialchorus.com/
W.L. Gore & Associates point of contact for this tool is Jamie Zingaro <jzingaro@wlgore.com>.

sn_value:
Per the vendor:
As a client user, the Viedoc 4 Export Application fetches CSV exports from Viedoc studies to allow for automated/scheduled data extraction to user specified directories.  

In addition to allowing scheduled, automated exports, this tool automatically extracts CSV files for ready consumption into SAS, R, or other statistical analytics software.  While Viedoc does have an API with some export functionality, it does now export in formats other than CDISC ODM XML which often prove difficult to use with SAS , R, and other statistical analytics software.

In addition to allowing scheduled, automated exports, this tool automatically extracts CSV files for ready consumption into SAS, R, or other statistical analytics software. sn_value: Desktop application for viewing, analyzing and reporting of multiple types of ultrasound images. Receives raw data from ultrasound machines and can store in DICOM format to the PACS. Mark McClaskey: These are not workstations behind a firewall supported by Philips. The EchoPAC BT12 software is a GE Healtcare workstation software that is installed on GE portable ultrasound machines. There is currently only one GE Vivid q model at the Science Center. There is an on going support contract in place with GE Healthcare to support and calibrate this machine and yes, the images taken are uploaded to TRIP/PACS. I agree with your assessment that this CI is supported by an external vendor and the Status of maintain makes the most sense.

sn_value:
Today's data management landscape is becoming increasingly complex, as data is spread out across many heterogeneous data systems (data warehouses, columnar databases, MPP engines, specialized data stores, SaaS/cloud applications, etc.) that can be in multiple locations (on-premises, cloud, etc.). This makes it difficult to offer a unified view of the data to business applications, and to guarantee that governance policies and rules are enforced across the data delivery chain. 

The Logical data fabric is a vision of a unified data delivery platform that abstracts access to multiple data systems for business consumers, hiding the complexity and exposing the data in business friendly formats, while at the same time guaranteeing the delivery of data according to predefined semantics and governance rules, solving the main issues described above. 

Data virtualization is the key technology to achieve the logical data fabric vision. As the only data integration style designed for distributed architectures, data virtualization provides a logical data access layer on top of multiple heterogeneous systems in hybrid, distributed architectures. Today, the data management ecosystem is distributed in nature, so a logical data access layer such as data virtualization is the best fit.

Denodo Platform is a significant step forward to achieve the vision of a logical data fabric. It incorporates features that accelerate the delivery of governed data to business applications, in the most appropriate format for each consumer, across multiple, geographically distributed, heterogeneous systems. Denodo Platform offers stronger support for core data virtualization use cases: logical analytical architectures, logical data warehouses, and data services APIs. But it goes beyond traditional data virtualization scenarios to better support new types of users and new types of use cases, such as data science and machine learning (ML) initiatives.

This makes it difficult to offer a unified view of the data to business applications, and to guarantee that governance policies and rules are enforced across the data delivery chain. sn_value:
This CI refers to a workstation computer which is referred to as ""USWBIOSTAT01"", as well as the surrounding components which support a set of automated processes.  

On this workstation SAS is used as a processing engine, SAS is installed on the computer and there are Windows Scheduled Tasks which are responsible for initiating a number of SAS programs.  All scheduled tasks are run by the logged-in user "USW\BiostatAuto".  

The password of this account is known by the Clinical Biostat team.  The computer is run "headless" (meaning without a monitor attached), and an RDP session is used to log the account in, after which the session is disconnected (and the account stays logged in, in order to continue running the scheduled tasks.)

At this point (06/23/20) the only automated processes are SAS reports which are generated automatically via Task Scheduler using the USW\BiostatAuto account.  After the reports are generated, they are sent via smtp through smtp.wlgore.com.
The Medrio and Medidata FTP functionality has been replaced with the functionality in the CI "IntEco_Clinical_EDC_Export"

The workstation itself is hosted in the Route 66 facility.
Since this is a workstation provisioned with our Gore Standard Image, and is managed consistent with other workstations, the Kiltie Lane CSA team is responsible for support, however this is specifically supported by Melissa Poletti and Jake Gardner

The desktop computer is monitored with Solarwinds due to the expectations around availability.  
https://uswswnpm01.wlgore.com/Orion/NetPerfMon/NodeDetails.aspx?NetObject=N:1357

sn_value:
Azure AD Application Proxy is a service implemented by IT for application owners want to publish on-premises applications or data externally. Remote users who need access to internal apps or data can then access them in a secure manner.
"While not comprehensive, the list below illustrates some of the things you can enable by implementing App Proxy in a hybrid coexistence scenario:

Publish on-premises web apps externally in a simplified way without a DMZ
Support single sign-on (SSO) across devices, resources, and apps in the cloud and on-premises
Support multi-factor authentication for apps in the cloud and on-premises
Quickly leverage cloud features with the security of the Microsoft Cloud
Centralize user account management
Centralize control of identity and security
Automatically add or remove user access to applications based on group membership"
collibra_value: Azure AD Application Proxy is a service implemented by IT for application owners want to publish on-premises applications or data externally. Remote users who need access to internal apps or data can then access them in a secure manner.  "While not comprehensive, the list below illustrates some of the things you can enable by implementing App Proxy in a hybrid coexistence scenario:    Publish on-premises web apps externally in a simplified way without a DMZ  Support single sign-on (SSO) across devices, resources, and apps in the cloud and on-premises  Support multi-factor authentication for apps in the cloud and on-premises  Quickly leverage cloud features with the security of the Microsoft Cloud  Centralize user account management  Centralize control of identity and security  Automatically add or remove user access to applications based on group membership"
